post_text:
Since 2009, the The Junior League of Austin Food in Tummies (FIT) program has helped provide nutritional support to @DelValleISD families through the delivery of weekend meal bags. Though many things about this school year are different, the Junior League of Austin (JLA)’s dedication to DVISD students has not changed.

JLA will continue to provide weekend meal bags to eligible DVISD families starting this Friday, September 11 from 7:30-11am for pickup at Baty Elementary Schools and Ojeda Middle. To ensure the safety of volunteers and food recipients, FIT has implemented COVID-19 safety measures including temperature screenings and mask-wearing policies during all packing shifts, deliveries and pickups.
text:
Since 2009, the The Junior League of Austin Food in Tummies (FIT) program has helped provide nutritional support to @DelValleISD families through the delivery of weekend meal bags. Though many things about this school year are different, the Junior League of Austin (JLA)’s dedication to DVISD students has not changed.

JLA will continue to provide weekend meal bags to eligible DVISD families starting this Friday, September 11 from 7:30-11am for pickup at Baty Elementary Schools and Ojeda Middle. To ensure the safety of volunteers and food recipients, FIT has implemented COVID-19 safety measures including temperature screenings and mask-wearing policies during all packing shifts, deliveries and pickups.

post_text: Join us for eLEAD, our virtual after school experience. Students can visit our site to experience activities centered around their favorite LEAD classes. From workouts, to scavenger hunts, to book and movie recommendations, to online chess games, to leadership classes to amazing science experiments, students can follow along by themselves or with their whole family. All activities are able to be completed with materials found at home for little or no cost. New activities and experiences will be posted each week.

We know the first week of school was busy and you may not have had time to submit your #DVFirstWeek2020 pictures yet. That’s why we are accepting them all weekend long!

Submit your photo (.jpeg or .png preferred) via Facebook, Instagram or Twitter direct message or email to Lauren.IveyMuniz@dvisd.net. Please include home campus and full name for all students pictured.

Note: We will use these pictures on Facebook, Twitter, the DVISD website and other DVISD publications throughout the school year. To ensure privacy, students pictured must be under the same guardianship. Some editing may be required.

Submission disclaimer: Please include the first and last names and home campus of all students pictured. To ensure privacy, students pictured must be under the same guardianship. Some editing may be required.
text:

Parents, please send your student's first week photos to us for posting. We will use these pictures on Facebook, Twitter, the DVISD website and other DVISD publications throughout the school year. You can submit your student's photo (.jpeg or .png preferred) via Facebook, Instagram or Twitter direct message or email to Lauren.IveyMuniz@dvisd.net.

"We are excited to welcome our new neighbors Tesla into the DVISD community," said Del Valle ISD Board of Trustees President Rebecca Birch. "From the start, their support, generosity, and commitment to our students has been unwavering. Based on the overwhelmingly positive feedback at both of our public board meetings, this sentiment is shared not only with our board and Superintendent, but our community at large. As demonstrated in other locations, Tesla can make a big impact on student learning. We are looking forward to developing multiple pathways to enrich our students’ and community’s lives with programming and employment opportunities. We are confident that Tesla will be 'DV Proud' partnering with us on the journey of preparing students for a successful future."
#OpportunityAustin

post_text:
In response to Tesla looking to possibly build on land within the Del Valle Independent School District, Superintendent Dr. Annette Tielle released the following statement:
"On behalf of our students and teachers, we are excited by the prospect of a company of this magnitude coming to our district. This type of partnership could provide our students authentic, rigorous, and practical internship, apprenticeship, and work study programs in the areas of robotics, engineering, manufacturing, and STEM. Our focus has always been ensuring that our children have robust and successful futures. The addition of a company who has the ability to support our community both economically and academically would be advantageous for our students and accelerate our efforts to mentor and develop the workforce of the next generation.”
text:
In response to Tesla looking to possibly build on land within the Del Valle Independent School District, Superintendent Dr. Annette Tielle released the following statement:
"On behalf of our students and teachers, we are excited by the prospect of a company of this magnitude coming to our district. This type of partnership could provide our students authentic, rigorous, and practical internship, apprenticeship, and work study programs in the areas of robotics, engineering, manufacturing, and STEM. Our focus has always been ensuring that our children have robust and successful futures. The addition of a company who has the ability to support our community both economically and academically would be advantageous for our students and accelerate our efforts to mentor and develop the workforce of the next generation.”

post_text: Last night the DVISD Board of Trustees approved a resolution to initiate a process for the District to become a District of Innovation. The District is pursuing this designation in response to the COVID19 crisis so that we can start the school year one week earlier in order to minimize learning loss. Tomorrow (June 18) at 2:00PM, we will be hosting a public meeting to share the draft plan with the public and take public comment. For access information to the meeting, please visit the link below.

post_text:
Today, we salute our School Lunch Heroes! These heroes served about 27,000 meals to the children of our community today.

District leadership, School Board Secretary Elvia Guadian, and Board Members Ann Heuberger and Damian Pantoja visited each meal prep site, providing cupcakes and words of appreciation to recognize their dedication. Sodexo served the teams a barbecue meal for lunch.

We appreciate the families who shared their gratitude with our DVISD heroes! Have your own photos to share? Send them over in a private message and we'll share them on social media and with our meal teams.

post_text:
Tomorrow, we will celebrate School Lunch Hero Day! 🍎🍔

Please join us in recognizing the DVISD heroes who have continued to provide the children in our community healthy meals during the school closures.

We hope you will show your appreciation in a safe way when picking up your meals tomorrow. Consider giving a wave, displaying a thank you sign, or even dressing up as a superhero.

Thank you, Child Nutrition, Maintenance and Transportation staff, for your dedication to our schools and community!

Del Valle ISD is pleased to introduce eLEAD, our virtual after school experience. Students can visit our site to experience activities centered around their favorite LEAD classes. From workouts, to scavenger hunts, to book and movie recommendations, to online chess games, to leadership classes to amazing science experiments, students can follow along by themselves or with their whole family. All activities are able to be completed with materials found at home for little or no cost. New activities and experiences will be posted each week.

These resources are open to all students in DVISD, not just students currently enrolled in LEAD‼️

https://sites.google.com/delvalle-isd.org/lead/home

Your $5 donation could earn DVISD Education Partners an extra $1000!

If we obtain the most individual donors between 3 and 4 p.m. today, we can earn an extra $1000 from Amplify Austin.

Donations as small as $5 count! Please visit bit.ly/amplifydv2020 to make your donation now!

ALSO: By adding #LoveTitos in your donation message at checkout, an extra $5 will be added to your donation.

post_text:
Del Valle Education Partners is participating in I Live Here I Give Here's Amplify Austin Day, which is running now through 6 p.m. tomorrow, March 6. Your donations support scholarships, grants, and recognition programs for the students and staff of DVISD!

Learn more and donate now at https://www.amplifyatx.org/organizations/del-valle-isd-education-partners

Del Valle ISD teachers, instructional aides and administrators participated in a staff-led professional development mini-conference today which showcased the best ideas and instructional practices that are currently being implemented by DVISD teachers.

"Every year we get feedback from teachers about the great things their peers are doing in the classroom and with students. This is that special place where we get to showcase it for all to see,” said Del Valle ISD Executive Director of Curriculum & Instruction Sonja Howard.

This includes tutoring, LEAD afterschool activities, athletic practices and games, and Extend-A-Care. Parents are being asked to pick-up your student(s) as soon as possible when the school day ends.
